:{{A|VO chapter4 29 aglaea 117.ogg}} '''Aglaea:''' You are the only life she ever saved by her own hand in her one thousand years on this earth. I believe no one is more qualified for this noble task.
:{{DIcon|Arrow}} Let the ceremony begin.
:{{A|VO chapter4 29 trinnon 101.ogg}} '''Trinnon:''' O! Gods who have returned, and gods who are still watching! Today, we bring you a soul laid bare.
:{{A|VO chapter4 29 trinnon 102.ogg}} '''Trinnon:''' The Hand of Shadow, Thanatos, remembered their name from the past! From daylight they came and to their fragrant dwelling they return, to walk now among your ranks.
:{{A|VO chapter4 29 trinnon 103 m.ogg}} {{A|VO chapter4 29 trinnon 103 f.ogg}} '''Trinnon:''' And there was one who joined hands with the Titan. A traveler risen from the dead and reborn among mortal kind. {{MC|m=He|f=She}} is the everlasting night and shall now proclaim in {{MC|m=his|f=her}} good name:
:{{A|VO chapter4 29 trinnon 104.ogg}} '''Trinnon:''' "O majesty of the Twelve Titans, pillars of the world&mdash;"
:{{A|VO chapter4 29 trinnon 105.ogg}} '''Trinnon:''' "We seek your divinity, to mend the rifts of the world &mdash;"
:{{A|VO chapter4 29 trinnon 106.ogg}} '''Trinnon:''' "Fill our bodies with blood of gold, till we wither in willing service to the prophecy..."
:{{A|VO chapter4 29 trinnon 107.ogg}} '''Trinnon:''' Step forward, Trailblazer from beyond the sky. And together with '''us'''...
:{{A|VO chapter4 29 trinnon 108.ogg}} '''Trinnon:''' Surrender the Coreflame and carve their star into the sky.
:{{DIcon|Arrow}} Surrender the Coreflame.
:{{DIcon|Arrow}} Goodbye, Castorice.
