::{{A|VO chapter4 29 anaxa 119.ogg}} '''Anaxa:''' Heh, she made quite a scene. I suppose it's my turn now.
::{{A|VO chapter4 29 aglaea 118.ogg}} '''Aglaea:''' I won't stop you...
::{{A|VO chapter4 29 phainon 109.ogg}} '''Phainon:''' Professor, you...
::{{A|VO chapter4 29 anaxa 120.ogg}} '''Anaxa:''' What's with that look? You were present.
::{{A|VO chapter4 29 anaxa 121.ogg}} '''Anaxa:''' So, let's get this execution over with. We wouldn't want to bring shame to Okhema's divine laws or keep me from creating a new world.
::{{A|VO chapter4 29 phainon 110.ogg}} '''Phainon:''' You never change, do you, Professor?
::{{A|VO chapter4 29 phainon 111.ogg}} '''Phainon:''' I don't understand. If your theory is correct, you'll lose all memories of your past life once you become a Titan, so what's the point of becoming a god?
::{{A|VO chapter4 29 anaxa 122.ogg}} '''Anaxa:''' Of course there's a point. Even if I forget who I am, I'll still have my brilliant mind.
::{{A|VO chapter4 29 anaxa 123.ogg}} '''Anaxa:''' It goes without saying I'll find a way to retrieve memories of my past life. Besides, I still have you, don't I?
::{{A|VO chapter4 29 phainon 112.ogg}} '''Phainon:''' I still don't really understand what you said during the assembly. Even if it were true, things reforged from memory could never be the same as the original anyway.
::{{A|VO chapter4 29 anaxa 124.ogg}} '''Anaxa:''' Then allow me to tell you right now that you're wrong.
::{{A|VO chapter4 29 anaxa 125.ogg}} '''Anaxa:''' What exactly are we? My answer is that the Chrysos Heirs are the future Titans, and vice versa. Of course, this answer only applies to us.
::{{A|VO chapter4 29 anaxa 126.ogg}} '''Anaxa:''' So, what are "we" when it comes to regular mortals?
::{{A|VO chapter4 29 anaxa 127.ogg}} '''Anaxa:''' {{Color|keyword|nobold=1|The very essence of the world &mdash; our souls &mdash; are tiny invisible seeds that hold records of each person's memories of the world, and "we" are the buds that sprout from these seeds to grow into great trees.}}
::{{A|VO chapter4 29 phainon 113.ogg}} '''Phainon:''' Is that what Nousporism means?
::{{A|VO chapter4 29 anaxa 128.ogg}} '''Anaxa:''' Correct. Once our physical bodies are born, we become new extensions of the world. From there, we plant our seeds into someone's memories and then scatter them into the hearts of countless people in the future.
::{{A|VO chapter4 29 anaxa 129.ogg}} '''Anaxa:''' Just as seeds are affected by their environment, so too will our appearances differ across memories. But the partial memories we carry will always be the same, because that is just how the world is.
::{{A|VO chapter4 29 anaxa 130.ogg}} '''Anaxa:''' To destroy our very existence, one must destroy the world itself. But we have someone who will still live on with his perfect memory...
::{{A|VO chapter4 29 anaxa 131.ogg}} '''Anaxa:''' That person is you, child of Kephale. This is what it means to be the Worldbearing Titan.
::{{A|VO chapter4 29 anaxa 132.ogg}} '''Anaxa:''' So, carry everything of this world and live on. Don't disappoint those most precious to you. Don't disappoint Lady Goldweaver.
::{{A|VO chapter4 29 anaxa 133.ogg}} '''Anaxa:''' And especially don't bring dishonor to my theory.
::{{A|VO chapter4 29 phainon 114.ogg}} '''Phainon:''' ...
::{{A|VO chapter4 29 phainon 115.ogg}} '''Phainon:''' Anaxa, I swear to you. I'll lead everyone to our reunion in the new world.
::{{A|VO chapter4 29 anaxa 134.ogg}} '''Anaxa:''' Hmph, good.
::{{A|VO chapter4 29 anaxa 135.ogg}} '''Anaxa:''' That's all I have to say. Farewell, everyone. May we meet again in the next life.
::{{A|VO chapter4 29 aglaea 119.ogg}} '''Aglaea:''' Farewell, Great Performer. May Cerces safeguard your thoughts.
::{{DIcon|Arrow}} Salute him in the same way.
